BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260320T101640Z
UID:bwnp-x3ixm04f5wj7-ev-sw31f-20260125110000
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260125T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260125T170000
DESCRIPTION:Join us for the first event in our Hullabaloo workshop series
 —an afternoon of hands-on making\, creative experimentation\, and good c
 ompany at the makerspace.\nThis lamp-making workshop is all about personal
  expression. Participants are invited to bring an existing lamp\, lamp sha
 de\, or found objects—or start fresh using provided materials—to creat
 e a one-of-a-kind light that fits their style and space. Whether you’re 
 into subtle design tweaks or bold\, colorful statements\, this workshop is
  designed to be accessible\, playful\, and exploratory.\nWe’ll support t
 hree creative paths during the workshop:\nCustomize a lamp shade by adding
  textures\, colors\, patterns\, or design elements to transform its look a
 nd mood.\nRefurbish an existing lamp\, experimenting with finishes\, mater
 ials\, and structural changes to give it new life.\nBuild a lamp using LED
  lighting\, creating colorful or animated effects that add personality and
  motion to your design.\nNo prior experience is required. This workshop is
  beginner-friendly\, with guidance available throughout\, and plenty of ro
 om for experimentation. Come for the pastries\, stay for the making\, and 
 leave with a lamp that’s entirely your own.\nYou are encouraged to visit
  thrift shops for ideas and discover items which are already lamps or aspi
 re to become a lamp. You'll know if when you see it. See you on the 25th!\
 n\n\nhttps://bookwhen.com/sequoiafabrica/e/ev-sw31f-20260125110000
LOCATION:1736 18th Street\, San Francisco CA 94107-2343
ORGANIZER:mailto:info@sequoiafabrica.org
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Hullabaloo: Lamp Making Workshop
URL:https://bookwhen.com/sequoiafabrica/e/ev-sw31f-20260125110000
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260320T101640Z
UID:bwnp-x3ixm04f5wj7-ev-sn5u9-20260126190000
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260126T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260126T203000
DESCRIPTION:In this class we will be discussing how to successfully read a 
 sewing pattern! We won't be sewing\, but will do a table read of a few pat
 terns. If you have a pattern in mind\, feel free to bring it. \nWhat we wi
 ll cover:\n- Where to find patterns\n- What to look for in a good pattern\
 n- Key vocab words to help you understand pattern steps \n- How to print p
 attern pieces\n- How to layout pattern pieces\n\n\nhttps://bookwhen.com/se
 quoiafabrica/e/ev-sn5u9-20260126190000
LOCATION:1736 18th Street\, San Francisco CA 94107-2343
ORGANIZER:mailto:info@sequoiafabrica.org
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:How to Read a Sewing Pattern
URL:https://bookwhen.com/sequoiafabrica/e/ev-sn5u9-20260126190000
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
