BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260320T101640Z
UID:bwnp-x3ixm04f5wj7-ev-sh2yu-20260221130000
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260221T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260221T153000
DESCRIPTION:Join us for this two-part series where you will learn the basic
 s of parametric 3D CAD modeling and 3D printing to design and print your o
 wn organizer or trinket tray!\nPart 1: Introduction to parametric 3D CAD -
  February 21\nPart 2: Introduction to 3D printing - February 28\nPart 1 wi
 ll cover basics of parametric modeling\, including:\n- How parametric mode
 ling works and how it differs from mesh modeling\n- Resources and programs
  for both\n- Basic functions and workflow for parametric modeling\n- How t
 o visualize and capture everyday objects for parametric modeling\n- Practi
 cal portion: use a free 3D modeling program to create a custom organizer o
 r trinket tray!\nPart 2 will cover basics of 3D printing\, including:\n- H
 ow to find existing models\n- Different types of 3D printing\n- How fused-
 deposition modeling (FDM) printing works and how to design for this proces
 s\n- How to prepare and slice a 3D print file\n- How to run and troublesho
 ot an FDM 3D printer\n- Practical portion: design for manufacturing (DFM) 
 edits and design changes to the 3D model created in part 1 to prepare the 
 part for printing!\nFiles for printing will be submitted at the end of Par
 t 2. Parts will be printed after class and ready for pickup starting the n
 ext day!\nAge 12+ recommended\, minors must attend with an adult\n\n\nhttp
 s://bookwhen.com/sequoiafabrica/e/ev-sh2yu-20260221130000
LOCATION:1736 18th Street\, San Francisco CA 94107-2343
ORGANIZER:mailto:info@sequoiafabrica.org
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Fabrication: Design and 3D Print an Organizer. Part 1.
URL:https://bookwhen.com/sequoiafabrica/e/ev-sh2yu-20260221130000
END:VEVENT
