DTSTAMP:20260320T101640Z
UID:bwnp-x3ixm04f5wj7-ev-slz3z-20260319180000
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260319T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260319T200000
DESCRIPTION:Whether you are an experienced printmaker\, or new to the craft
 \, join us in the workshop for an evening to socialize\, meet other makers
 \, make some messes\, and hopefully some art 🎨🧑‍🎨!\nThis casual
  event will give you the opportunity to flex your creative muscles. We wil
 l have supplies and materials available for experimenting\, and bringing y
 our ideas to life.\nDon't know where to start or what to make? We also hav
 e prefabricated stamps as examples for you to practice printing with.\nThi
 s event is primarily focused on block prints\, which is a type of relief p
 rintmaking (https://ldart.work/printing-relief-techniques-parts-1-to-7/).\
 nThis social often has a waiting list. Please cancel your ticket if you ar
 e not able to attend in order to make room for another student.\n\n\nhttps
 ://bookwhen.com/sequoiafabrica/e/ev-slz3z-20260319180000
LOCATION:1736 18th Street\, San Francisco CA 94107-2343
ORGANIZER:mailto:info@sequoiafabrica.org
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Block Printmaking Social
URL:https://bookwhen.com/sequoiafabrica/e/ev-slz3z-20260319180000
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260320T101640Z
UID:bwnp-x3ixm04f5wj7-ev-shi2p-20260326190000
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260326T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260326T210000
DESCRIPTION:Are you a knitter and curious about knitting machines? Are you 
 generally curious about how knitting machines function? Are you interested
  in fiber arts or clothes making and want to expand your range of tools? T
 his workshop is for you!\nIn this class you will make a scarf. Skills you 
 will learn include:\ncasting on\;\nbasic operation\;\nchanging yarns\;\nca
 sting off\;\nfinishing and assembly techniques.\nKnitting machines are ama
 zing pieces of equipment able to replicate virtually all hand knitting pat
 terns - at a much faster pace. We will demonstrate a range of knitting mac
 hines\, flat and circular\, manual and computerized\, and will teach you t
 he basic operations on a home knitting machine. This knowledge can be appl
 ied to more complex machines. You can then use our knitting machine during
  our open project classes\, open workshop hours\, when you become a member
 \, or we can help you procure your own.\n\n\nhttps://bookwhen.com/sequoiaf
 abrica/e/ev-shi2p-20260326190000
LOCATION:1736 18th Street\, San Francisco CA 94107-2343
ORGANIZER:mailto:info@sequoiafabrica.org
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Knit a Scarf: Introduction to Machine Knitting
URL:https://bookwhen.com/sequoiafabrica/e/ev-shi2p-20260326190000
END:VEVENT
